The paper focuses on the usability and user acceptance of two-factor authentication in online banking, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and security (CR). The study also collected qualitative and quantitative data, which falls under social and information sciences (SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the perceived security of 2FA, which is related to cybersecurity (CY) and software engineering (SE).
